  - paragraph: "It’s an unfortunate reality that the risk of developing some form of dementia rises as you grow older. According to the Alzheimer’s Association, an estimated 55 million people worldwide live with dementia, with Alzheimer’s disease being the most common type. And Alzheimer’s Association research shows that the greatest risk factor for developing the disease is age:"
